<FIRST>r a BC-Quotes     04-07 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Quotes,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``It's awful to see when you think that these people have no
lives. It's very sad.'' _ Former first lady Nancy Reagan after
accompanying police on a late-night raid of a suspected drug house
in Los Angeles.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``We had been stripped of our dignity while we were working for
Frank Lorenzo _ now we have it back, and we are going to rebuild
the airline.'' _ Eastern mechanic Jorge Martinez commenting after a
group led by former baseball commission Peter Ueberroth agreed to
buy Eastern and give employees 30 percent of the company in
exchange for concessions.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``It's going to be big, we hope big enough for the Supreme Court
to realize that if they reverse their ruling, it would cause total
chaos in this society.'' _ Molly Yard, president of the National
Organization for Women, commenting on a planned weekend rally in
Washington by supporters of legalized abortion.
