<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SpyArrests     04-07 0152</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Spy Arrests,0156</SECOND>
<HEAD>Couple Arrested For Allegedly Giving Armaments Technology to East</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A West German couple has been
arrested on suspicion of espionage for allegedly transferring
armaments-related technical equipment to the East bloc, a police
spokesman said Friday.
   Peter Raisch of the Baden-Wuerttemberg state police in Stuttgart
identifed the couple only as a 53-year-old man and his 52-year-old
wife.
   Raisch said that an arrest warrant had been issued on the man in
November, but he could not be arrested until he returned to West
Germany on April 2.
   Further investigation led police to arrest the man's wife
Tuesday in Sigmaringen, about 50 miles south of Stuttgart, Raisch
said.
   He declined to reveal which East bloc country they allegedly
dealt with, or where the man had been prior to his arrest.
   Raisch would identify the electronic equipment only as
``technical equipment that can be used for armaments.''
