<SECOND>AM-BRF--Relics,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Stolen 12th Century Church Statue Found in Garage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PERUGIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said they found a 12th century
wooden statue and 270 artifacts stolen from a church last year in a
garage on the outskirts of Perugia.
   Three people were brought in for questioning about the theft of
the 49-inch high ``Madonna with Child'' and other artifacts, news
agencies said.
   The statue, carved by an unknown artist in the 12th century, was
among the itmes stolen from the church of Santa Maria in Camuccia
in the hillside town of Todi, 60 miles northeast of Rome, in 1988.
   Thieves entered the church through the basement during an
archaeological excavation and dismantled an alarm system in the
chapel where the statue was displayed, news reports said.
</TEXT>
