<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--GangOlympics     04-07 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Gang Olympics,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>Community Leader Organizing Gang Olympics</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A community leader in Los Angeles wants to
organize a form of Olympics for gang members to curtail violence
that often occurs during summer.
   ``We want to take the Uzis and AK-47s out of the hands of the
young members of our community and put shot puts and javelins in
their place,'' the Rev. Charles Mims said Thursday.
   The games, scheduled July 10 through Aug. 18, are to include
academic as well as athletic events and will be open to contestants
aged 12 to 18, said Mims.
   Events are to be organized so that members of opposing gangs are
on the same teams, in an effort to build tolerance between rivals,
Mims said.
