<HEAD>Fixed-Rate Mortgage Rates Slip from Last Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages are currently
averaging 11.07 percent, according to a national survey released
Friday by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That rate was down from a rate of 11.19 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 9.39 percent this week, up from 9.31
percent the week before, Freddie Mac said.
