<FIRST>r f BC-Emery-CFMerger     04-07 0213</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Emery-CF Merger,0220</SECOND>
<HEAD>Consolidated Freightways Purchase Of Emery Completed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MENLO PARK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Consolidated Freightways Inc.'s
acquisition of Emery Air Freight Corp. of Wilton, Conn., became
official Thursday, company officials said.
   Consolidated Freightways undertook a cash tender offer of $230
million for all of Emery's common and preferred shares. As of
Thursday, more than 90 percent of the common shares and 90 percent
of the preferred shares had been acquired, allowing completion of
the merger, the company said.
   The combined company will have annual revenues of more than $4
billion. It will deploy more than 80 aircraft and operate one of
the industry's most advanced freight-sorting centers in Dayton,
Ohio, the company said.
   ``With our capabilities through a combined network of more than
450 air freight terminals in North America and 88 countries around
the world, we will provide the shipping customer with unmatched
service on a global scale,'' said Larry R. Scott, president and
chief executive officer of Consolidated and chairman of the new
company.
   All facilities, administration and operations of Emery Air
Freight and CF Air Freight will be merged by May 1, company
officials said.
   Consolidated Freightways is a diversified transportation company
with businesses in long-haul and regional trucking, air freight,
ocean container freight and rail piggyback services.
</TEXT>
